Categories/NSError%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: KST_alertMessage
Categories/NSError%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Returns the value for the KSTErrorAlertMessageKey key in the receiver’s userInfo dictionary if non-nil, then the value for the NSLocalizedDescriptionKey key, then KST_defaultAlertMessage.

Categories/NSDictionary%28KSTExtensions%.name: -KST_dictionaryByAddingDictionaryEntries:
Categories/NSDictionary%28KSTExtensions%.abstract: Returns a new dictionary by adding the entries from dictionary to the receiver.

Categories/NSDate%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.name: -KST_day
Categories/NSDate%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.abstract: Returns the day component from a NSDateComponents created from the receiver.

Categories/NSDate%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.name: -KST_month
Categories/NSDate%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.abstract: Returns the month component from a NSDateComponents created from the receiver.

Categories/NSDate%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.name: -KST_year
Categories/NSDate%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.abstract: Returns the year component from a NSDateComponents created from the receiver.

Categories/NSDate%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.name: -KST_beginningOfDay
Categories/NSDate%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.abstract: Returns a NSDate representing the beginning of the day, which is 12:00:00 AM.

Categories/NSDate%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.name: -KST_endOfDay
Categories/NSDate%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.abstract: Returns a NSDate representing the end of the day, which is 11:59:59 PM.

Categories/NSData%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.name: -KST_SHA1String
Categories/NSData%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.abstract: Creates and returns an NSString representing the SHA1 hash of the receiver’s bytes.

Categories/NSData%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.name: -KST_SHA256String
Categories/NSData%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.abstract: Creates and returns an NSString representing the SHA256 hash of the receiver’s bytes.

Categories/NSData%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.name: -KST_SHA512String
Categories/NSData%28KSTExtensions%29.htm.abstract: Creates and returns an NSString representing the SHA512 hash of the receiver’s bytes.

Categories/NSCharacterSet%28KSTExtension.name: KST_allStrings
Categories/NSCharacterSet%28KSTExtension.abstract: Returns an array containing every string in the receiver.

Categories/NSBundle%28KSTExtensions%29.h.name: KST_currentBundle
Categories/NSBundle%28KSTExtensions%29.h.abstract: Returns the current bundle based on the calling context. For example, if you call this property within a framework, it will return the framework bundle. If you call this property in the main app, it will return the main bundle.

Categories/NSBundle%28KSTExtensions%29.h.name: -KST_bundleDisplayName
Categories/NSBundle%28KSTExtensions%29.h.abstract: Returns the bundle display name. For example, “App”. This value is localized.

Categories/NSBundle%28KSTExtensions%29.h.name: -KST_bundleExecutable
Categories/NSBundle%28KSTExtensions%29.h.abstract: Returns the bundle executable. For example, “App”. This value is not localized.

Categories/NSBundle%28KSTExtensions%29.h.name: -KST_bundleShortVersionString
Categories/NSBundle%28KSTExtensions%29.h.abstract: Returns the bundle short version string. For example, “1.0.0”.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_reversedArray
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Creates and returns an NSArray with the receiver’s objects in reverse order.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_arrayByAppendingObject:
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Create and return an array by appending object onto the receiver.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_arrayByAppendingArray:
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Creates and returns an array by appending the objects from array onto the receiver.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_arrayByPrependingObject:
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Create and return an array by prepending object onto the receiver.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_arrayByPrependingArray:
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Creates and returns an array by prepending the objects from array onto the receiver.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_arrayByRemovingArray:
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Create and return an array by removing the objects in the provided array.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_set
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Creates and returns an NSArray with the receiver’s objects.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_mutableSet
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Creates and returns an NSMutableSet with the receiver’s objects.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_orderedSet
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Returns an NSOrderedSet with the receiver’s objects.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_mutableOrderedSet
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Returns an NSMutableOrderedSet with the receiver’s objects.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_shuffledArray
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Creates and returns a shuffled copy of the receiver.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_objectAtRandomIndex
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Returns the object at a random index in the receiver.

Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.name: -KST_safeObjectAtIndex:
Categories/NSArray%28KSTExtensions%29.ht.abstract: Returns the object at the provided index if index is within the receiver’s bounds, otherwise returns nil.

Categories/NSCharacterSet%28KSTPhoneNumb.name: KST_phoneNumberFormattedCharacterSet
Categories/NSCharacterSet%28KSTPhoneNumb.abstract: The complete set of characters KSTPhoneNumberFormatter allows in formatted string representations of phone numbers.

Categories/NSCharacterSet%28KSTPhoneNumb.name: KST_phoneNumberRoutingCharacterSet
Categories/NSCharacterSet%28KSTPhoneNumb.abstract: The complete set of characters that affect the routing of the phone number. This is defined as @“0123456789” + @“abcdABCD+*#”.

Categories/NSCharacterSet%28KSTPhoneNumb.name: KST_phoneNumberDecimalCharacterSet
Categories/NSCharacterSet%28KSTPhoneNumb.abstract: The decimal digits allowed in phone numbers. This is defined as @“0123456789”.
